{\b1 \qc \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \fs20 \li0 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb400 
PLAINTIFFS\rquote  MOTION FOR PARTIAL SUMMARY JUDGMENT REGARDING \u8220\'3fFIDUCIARY DUTIES\u8221\'3f AND \u8220\'3fBUSINESS JUDGMENT RULE\u8221\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
This matter arises from a verified complaint filed on July 17, 2002 by Plaintiffs, William Robertson (\u8220\'3fMr. Robertson\u8221\'3f), Robert Halligan (\u8220\'3fMr. Halligan\u8221\'3f), Anne R. Meier, and Katherine Ernst. (collectively \u8220\'3fPlaintiffs\u8221\'3f). against Defendants, Shirley M. Tilghman, John J.F. Sherrerd, Peter Wendell, and Stephen Oxman (collectively the \u8220\'3fUniversity-designated Trustees\u8221\'3f), Princeton University (the \u8220\'3fUniversity\u8221\'3f) (collectively \u8220\'3fDefendants\u8221\'3f), and the Robertson Foundation (the \u8220\'3fFoundation\u8221\'3f). Plaintiffs filed an amended verified complaint on November 12, 2004. On December 22, 2004, Defendants filed their answer and affirmative defenses. By way of the present motion, Plaintiffs seek to have the Court determine: (1) that the University and the University-designated Trustees have fiduciary obligations to the Foundation, including a special fiduciary duty to advance the Foundation\rquote s specific mission and protect its assets; and (2) that Defendants\rquote  actions are not entitled to the deference typically granted under the business judgment rule, but rather Defendants must prove the \u8220\'3fentire fairness\u8221\'3f of their actions.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
In and around 1960, Marie Robertson (\u8220\'3fMs. Robertson\u8221\'3f), an heir of the founder of the Great Atlantic & Pacific Tea Company (\u8220\'3fA&P\u8221\'3f), decided to donate 700,000 shares of A&P stock to the University. Ms. Robertson\rquote s husband, Charles Robertson, was a member of the University Class of 1926.
}
