Additionally, contrary to Plaintiffs\rquote  position, the Court finds the limited partnership cases relied on by Defendants to be at the very least instructive. Plaintiffs place great emphasis on the fact that in the context of limited partnerships the duty of loyalty can be removed in its entirety. The Court, however, does not interpret Defendants\rquote  citing to such cases as support for that proposition, but rather for the proposition that a mere structural conflict of interest should not automatically give way to an entire fairness standard of review. For instance, in 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
