Defendants also take issue with Plaintiffs\rquote  position that the University \u8220\'3fhas used Foundation money to build a jointly appointed School faculty that cares more about their respective academic disciplines (and the Foundation\rquote s money) than about the Foundation\rquote s mission.\u8221\'3f (Plaintiffs\rquote  Opposition Brief, at 41.) According to Defendants, jointly appointed School faculty benefits the School and enhances the Foundation\rquote s mission. On this point, Defendants\rquote  expert, Professor Nye observed:
