There are pros and cons on both sides of the joint appointment model for a professional school. The negative side stressed by Palmer is that academic disciplines might capture the resources of the professional school and prevent appointments that do not fill their disciplinary needs. The positive side, which has been part of the Princeton model from the start, is that the prospect for attracting a world class faculty to a professional school is enhanced if professors are also offered opportunities to be connected with their disciplinary departments. This stronger faculty attracts other first rate faculty as well as first rate students. There is no question that Princeton has attracted first class faculty with its joint appointments.
\par 
