 at 198\u8221\'3f.) Defendants also note that Plaintiffs\rquote  characterization of President Tilghman\rquote s deposition testimony is inaccurate, as she testified that \u8220\'3fthe joint appointment system has been a tremendous benefit .. [a]nd I think it will continue to benefit the ... School .. [by] attract[ing] much stronger faculty than they would have been able to do had they only been offering school-only appointments.\u8221\'3f (Cert. of Mr. Bartlett, Exh, \u8220\'3f88\u8221\'3f, at T231 and T233.) Therefore, Defendants maintain that there remains no reason to doubt the University\rquote s ability to produce a School with objectives entirely consistent with those of the Foundation.
\par 
