{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The issue before the Court is whether to grant Defendants\rquote  motion for partial summary judgment that the University is the \u8220\'3fsole beneficiary\u8221\'3f under the Foundation\rquote s Certificate of Incorporation, thereby foreclosing Plaintiffs\rquote  requested remedy of severing the relationship between the University and the Foundation. Under R. 4:46-2, summary judgment is only appropriate where the pleadings, affidavits; and other matters of record show that there is no genuine issue as to material fact and the moving party is entitled to judgment as a matter of law. 
}
