{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Here, the Court declines to make a dispositive ruling at this stage concerning whether the equitable doctrines of cy pres and deviation apply in the present matter. Essentially, the Court need only reach the issue of applying the equitable doctrines of cy pres and deviation in the event that Plaintiffs are unsuccessful in their allegations of egregious behavior by Defendants for the Court to exercise its equitable powers to provide Plaintiffs with the relief it seeks. In connection with this, the Court is not satisfied, at this stage in the litigation, that there has been a sufficient showing of a legal or practical impediment to the accomplishment of the Foundation\rquote s mission as set forth in the Foundation\rquote s Certificate of Incorporation. In fact, the parties have yet to even seek a dispositive ruling on the parameters of the Foundation\rquote s mission. Therefore, a dispositive ruling on the applicability of these doctrines is unnecessary, and it would be imprudent of the Court to make such-a finding without first making ultimate findings of fact, and having an opportunity to appreciate the underpinnings of such facts.
